The accessibility tree shows that the 'Zoom In' link (bid 406) is still available and focused. To see even more detailed road information, I'll click this button one more time to further increase the zoom level. This should show even finer details of roads, intersections, and possibly street names.

Looking at the image URLs in the accessibility tree, I can see they're currently using zoom level 12 (e.g., 'https://tile.openstreetmap.org/12/1192/1506.png'). After clicking zoom in again, these should change to level 13, showing more detailed tiles.
